author: CNN
description: A US federal government shutdown could mean significant travel disruptions, closures to national parks and uncertainty for federal workers – but every government shutdown differs somewhat. Typically, functions that are critical to the protection of lives and property are deemed essential and remain open. CNN’s Brian Todd takes a look at previous government shutdowns to give us a clue what services are likely to remain open, and resources that could be halted.
title: How a government shutdown may impact you

author: CNN
description: Tilly Norwood is an AI-generated computer character that has drawn swift reactions from the Hollywood community after it was announced that talent agents were looking to sign the AI “actress”.
title: New AI actress sparks backlash from Hollywood

author: CNN
description: Five homes collapsed into the Atlantic Ocean in Buxton, North Carolina’s Outer Banks as surf from two hurricanes passing offshore battered the region.
title: Homes collapse into ocean from heavy hurricane surf

author: CNN
description: During his speech to generals and admirals in Quantico, President Donald Trump recalled a moment when he ordered two nuclear submarines to be strategically positioned near Russia in response to what he said were aggressive remarks by Dmitry Medvedev, the country’s former president and current deputy chairman of its Security Council. He then went on to say 'nuclear' was one of the two N-words Americans can't use.
title: Trump: Two 'N-words and you can't use either of them'

author: CNN
description: Former CNN president Tom Johnson joins Wolf Blitzer and Pamela Brown to discuss his new book "Driven: A Life in Public Service and Journalism from LBJ to CNN." Former CNN anchor Judy Woodruff, who wrote the foreword to the book, also joins them. They discuss CNN's Gulf War coverage and Johnson's long career. #CNN #News
title: Former CNN president reflects on his front-row seat to history

author: CNN
description: After another deadly Israeli strike on Gaza City, rescuers are searching for beloved local teacher Ghada Rabah, who is believed to be trapped in the rubble of her home.
title: Rescuers search for missing teacher who may be in rubble after strike

author: CNN
description:
It's a rare sight: Hurricanes Imelda and Humberto are churning off the US East Coast, separated from each other by only 450 miles. This is the closest a pair of hurricanes have been to each other in more than 50 years of satellite observations.
#cnn #news
title: Twin hurricanes are spinning in the Atlantic

author: CNN
description:
“It’s anarchy out there,” President Trump said last week in the Oval Office, days before announcing the federalization of 200 members of the Oregon National Guard for a period of 60 days. The president is citing daily protests outside the city’s Immigration and Customs Enforcement facility to justify the latest of his troop callups in a major city with a Democratic-led government. The state and the city government filed a lawsuit against the Trump administration Sunday, calling the president’s move “unlawful” and “baseless.”

CNN's Brianna Keilar speaks with Eric Zimmerman, Portland city councilor and lieutenant colonel in the Oregon National Guard. #CNN #News
title: Oregon sues Trump admin over National Guard deployment

author: CNN
description: CNN's Jeremy Diamond explains President Trump's 20-point peace plan to end the war in Gaza. Hamas has three to four days to respond to the deal, according to the president.
title: Hamas reviews US plan to end the war in Gaza

author: CNN
description: In a conversation with CNN's Dana Bash, former U.S. Senator Mitt Romney revealed that he called the White House during the Biden administration and urged the president to preemptively pardon Donald Trump.
title: Romney told Biden White House to pardon Trump

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Jake Tapper breaks down how the Riyadh Comedy Festival in Saudi Arabia is more than just a big topic of debate inside the comedy industry. Geopolitics and the kingdom’s “brutal repression of free speech” as Human Rights Watch puts it, contextualize the decision by comedians to perform at the festival. #cnn #news #shorts
title: Why the Riyadh Comedy Festival is more than just comics making a few jokes

author: CNN
description:
Thomas Jacob Sanford, the Marine veteran who killed at least four people and injured 8 others at the Michigan Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints on Sunday, harbored a deep resentment against the faith that stemmed from a breakup with an LDS girlfriend more than a decade ago, a childhood friend told CNN.

Pamela Brown speaks with CNN security correspondent Josh Campbell. #CNN #News
title: Friends: Michigan church gunman had grudge against Mormons

author: CNN
description: CNN senior reporter Daniel Dale fact-checks President Trump's speech to senior military officials at Quantico, Virginia. #CNN #News
title: 'There were just so many false claims': CNN's Daniel Dale fact-checks President Trump's speech

author: CNN
description: As President Donald Trump considers supplying Tomahawk missiles to Ukraine, CNN's Clare Sebastian explains what these weapons are capable of. #CNN #News
title: What are Tomahawk missiles?

author: CNN
description:
A strong earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 6.9 struck the Philippines, according to the US Geological Survey, raising fears about damage and the possibility of a localized tsunami. Video shows the quake rattling the Miss Asia Pacific International Gala Night event in Cebu.

#cnn #news #philippines #earthquake #pageant
title: 6.9 earthquake rattles pageant in Philippines

author: CNN
description: Major video game company, Electronic Arts, is going private after agreeing to sell itself in a record-setting deal to a group of investors, including Saudi Arabia's Public Investment Fund and Jared Kushner's Affinity Partners. CNN’s Max Foster explains. #CNN #news
title: Saudis and Kushner make major video game deal

author: CNN
description: Lindsey Halligan, the US attorney overseeing the prosecution of former FBI Director James Comey, once warned that the Department of Justice risked becoming a tool for political revenge. Today, Halligan is drawing criticism for leading one of the most politically charged prosecutions in decades. CNN's Andrew Kaczynski reports. #cnn #cnnnews
title: Trump-appointed Comey prosecutor once warned against political prosecution

author: CNN
description: Robert Wun's evocative and intricate designs have been upending expectations of luxury since he gained a rare place on the Paris Couture calendar in 2023. CNN visits his studio in east London to see how his creations take shape. #CNN #News
title: Meet the designer who burns his creations

author: CNN
description:
A possible shutdown of the federal government is just hours away as congressional lawmakers remain at odds over funding the government beyond September 30, the end of the fiscal year.

CNN's Kate Bolduan breaks down the possible impact of the shutdown, Alayna Treene reports from the White House, and John Berman speaks with Sen. Jeff Merkley (D-OR), ranking member of the Senate Budget Committee, about the looming shutdown and President Trump's possible deployment of the National Guard to Portland. #CNN #News
title: The federal government could shut down soon. Here's what you need to know.

author: CNN
description:
CNN’s Leigh Waldman sat down with Kris Johns, a candidate for local office, who described the "shocking" conversation he had with the man behind the attack on the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Grand Blanc Township, Michigan about a week before the attack.

#CNN #News #Michigan #LDS
title: Michigan church shooter compared Mormons to Antichrist

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump suggested that the US military should use US cities as training grounds. Retired Marine fighter pilot Amy McGrath explains why she thought that was the scariest part of Trump's speech to hundreds of generals and admirals.

#cnn #news #trump #usmilitary #military #pilot
title: Retired fighter pilot: This was the scariest part of Trump's speech

author: CNN
description:
Standing before a crowded auditorium of the US military’s senior officers, Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth vowed that the Defense Department could not “go another day without directly addressing the plank in our own eye,” in reference to what he called “social justice, politically correct, and toxic ideological garbage.”

CNN's John Berman speaks with retired Gen. Wesley Clark, former NATO Supreme Allied Commander. #CNN #News
title: Defense Secretary Hegseth: 'We became the Woke Department. But not anymore'

author: CNN
description: Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth told top military officers that he no longer wants to see “fat generals and admirals” or overweight troops in combat formations. Hegseth emphasized the importance of new fitness requirements for the US military.
title: Hegseth criticizes ‘fat troops’ and ‘fat generals’

author: CNN
description:
In a speech in front of hundreds of generals and admirals, Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth announced that US military service members in combat jobs will have to meet “this highest male standard only."

#cnn #news #hegseth #usmilitary #military
title: Hegseth: Combat troops will have to meet 'highest male standard'

author: CNN
description: "Why is it that the Democrats in my mind are facing more pressure?" CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten runs the numbers about political parties and their leaders. #CNN #News
title: Enten: 'Weak, weak, weak is how Democrats view their leaders in Washington'

author: CNN
description: Dramatic video shows severe flooding in Cullera, Spain on Monday. The flooding forms part of wider severe weather events in the region, alarming residents who experienced deadly flooding last year. #cnn #news
title: Severe flooding hits Spain

author: CNN
description:
Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth promised to end military diversity efforts in a speech before hundreds of generals and admirals in Quantico, Virginia.

#cnn #news #usmilitary #trump #petehegseth #military
title: Hegseth vows to end US military's diversity efforts

author: CNN
description: At least three people have been killed and 38 are missing under the rubble after a school building collapsed in Indonesia. Around a hundred were rescued from the building, that authorities say collapsed due to poor foundations under strain from construction.
title: Three killed in Indonesian school collapse

author: CNN
description:
As Americans see their energy bills rise, Rachel Cericola, a writer for the New York Times’ product review site Wirecutter, says that smart home technology could help lower your living expenses. She explains how you can solve everyday inconveniences with these gadgets and lower your utility bills at the same time.

Listen to the full episode of CNN’s Terms of Service podcast: http://swap.fm/l/tosyt091625

#cnn  #news #technology #smarthome
title: The surprising ways smart home technology helps save energy and money | Terms of Service

author: CNN
description: Nicole Kidman and Keith Urban have separated after nearly 20 years of marriage and are no longer living together in Nashville, Tennessee. The couple wed in 2006 and share two daughters. #cnn #nicolekidman #keithurban
title: Nicole Kidman and Keith Urban split

author: CNN
description: Afghanistan was plunged into a nationwide internet blackout, according to internet watchdog NetBlocks, with the Taliban taking more than 43 million citizens offline as part of what it describes as “morality measures.” CNN’s Ivan Watson explains what the shutdown means for Afghans living both inside the country and abroad. #CNN #News
title: Taliban cuts internet across Afghanistan

author: CNN
description: Kenqing Technology's innovation can make it easier to climb China's highest mountain. But not everybody is keen to try it. #cnn #news #robotics #china
title: Western influencer try Chinese-made robotic legs for hiking

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump shared a racist video on social media, which appears to be AI-generated, depicting House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries wearing a sombrero and a mustache and Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer speaking in a fake voice. Jeffries and Schumer met with Trump just hours before at the White House to discuss a looming government shutdown.
title: Trump posts racist, AI-generated video of Schumer and Jeffries

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Manu Raju spoke with lawmakers on Capitol Hill after democrats met with President Trump for last minute negotiations on the GOP-proposed funding bill as a government shutdown looms. #cnn, #news, #politics
title: Capitol Hill erupts ahead of likely government shutdown

author: CNN
description: Since the start of this year, dozens of scientists and researchers have left US institutions to take up full-time roles in China. This so-called "reverse brain drain" trend is not new, but comes amid a push from the Trump administration to cut federal research funding and as China aims to boost its global science and technology standing, with experts warning more talent could follow if US policy remains uncertain. CNN’s Simone McCarthy caught up with a Harvard professor emeritus who recently moved back to China. #cnn #news #china
title: Harvard professor explains his move to China

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Manu Raju spoke with lawmakers on Capitol Hill after democrats met with President Trump for last minute negotiations on the GOP-proposed funding bill as a government shutdown looms. #cnn, #news, #politics
title: Capitol Hill erupts ahead of likely government shutdown

author: CNN
description: CNN's Leigh Waldman reports from the scene of the shooting at The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints in Grand Blanc Township as investigators look to piece together a motive.
title: Officials work to determine motive in Michigan church shooting

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trumpfollowed through on his pledge to make Portland a target of his next National Guard deployment, saying in a social media post he was directing Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth to “provide all necessary troops” to Portland, a city he described as “war ravaged,” to protect ICE facilities he claimed are “under siege” by Antifa and “other domestic terrorists.” #CNN #News
title: Trump plans to send troops to 'war-ravaged' Portand, OR

author: CNN
description: Secretary Pete Hegseth has summoned hundreds of US generals and admirals for a meeting at the military instillation in Quantico, several US officials told CNN, though the reason for the meeting is unclear.
title: Hegseth orders senior military officials for unusual meeting at Quantico

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Erin Burnett spoke with Zohran Mamdani, New York City mayoral candidate, over a handful of issues, including Eric Adams dropping out of NYC mayoral race and President Trump's "communist" jab. #CNN #News
title: Mamdani: Trump is going through the 'stages of grief' due to my success
